      <title>Attendance Analyzer</title>
      <link>https://potterwhite.github.io/en/portfolio/attendance_analyzer/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://potterwhite.github.io/en/portfolio/attendance_analyzer/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;project-overview&#34;&gt;Project Overview&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The Attendance Analyzer is an &lt;strong&gt;in-house efficiency tool&lt;/strong&gt; developed to tackle the complex and time-consuming task of analyzing employee attendance data within a corporate environment. The application transforms raw Excel exports into clear, actionable reports via a highly flexible, rule-driven engine, significantly improving HR workflow efficiency.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;demo&#34;&gt;Demo&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Below is a short video demonstrating the application&amp;rsquo;s core workflow.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;    &#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;figure &gt;&#xA;    &#xA;        &#xA;&#xA;        &#xA;        &#xA;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;video-wrapper&#34; style=&#34;margin: auto; max-width: 800px;&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;video controls autoplay loop muted playsinline&#xA;                   style=&#34;width: 100%; height: auto; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;source src=&#34;https://potterwhite.github.io/2025/project_attendance_analyzer_show_video.mp4&#34; type=&#34;video/mp4&#34;&gt;&#xA;                Your browser does not support the video tag.&#xA;            &lt;/video&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&#xA;    &#xA;        &lt;figcaption style=&#34;text-align: center; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.5em; color: var(--td-sidebar-text-color);&#34;&gt;Application Core Workflow Demo&lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;core-features--tech-stack&#34;&gt;Core Features &amp;amp; Tech Stack&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rule-Driven Engine&lt;/strong&gt;: All logic is controlled by a &lt;code&gt;rules.toml&lt;/code&gt; file.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Comprehensive Metrics&lt;/strong&gt;: Calculates attended days, overtime, lateness, etc.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dual-View Reporting&lt;/strong&gt;: Generates both &amp;ldquo;Public&amp;rdquo; and &amp;ldquo;Detailed&amp;rdquo; reports.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tech Stack&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;strong&gt;Python&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Pandas&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Streamlit&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;TOML&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;core-algorithm-design-v16&#34;&gt;Core Algorithm Design (V1.6)&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;As the project&amp;rsquo;s architect, I designed a rigorous analysis algorithm based on a three-state unit model (&amp;ldquo;Attended&amp;rdquo;, &amp;ldquo;Absent&amp;rdquo;, &amp;ldquo;Abnormal&amp;rdquo;) and an &amp;ldquo;Attended Unit First&amp;rdquo; principle.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
